By way of derogation from Article 2, Member States shall authorise until 31 December 2006 the importation from third countries listed in Annex I of embryos complying with:
(a) the additional guarantees set out in the model veterinary certificate in Annex III; and
(b) the following conditions:
(i) embryos must be collected or produced before 1 January 2006;
(ii) embryos must only be used for implantation into female bovine animals resident in the Member State of destination indicated in the veterinary certificate;
(iii) embryos must not be subject to intra-Community trade.
